Welcome <%~ it.userName %>!

Your <%~ it.fellowshipType %> Fellowship Application Has Been Accepted

Dear <%~ it.userName %>,

We are thrilled to inform you that you have been selected for the Bitshala <%~ it.fellowshipType %> Fellowship! We're excited to see your impact and contributions and look forward to working with you over the months ahead.

We've set up a Google Drive folder (<%~ it.driveFolderUrl %>) where your contracts and tax forms will be collected. Your monthly work reports are submitted through the Bitshala app at https://app.bitshala.org/.

---

Next Steps

1. Sign the Contract
   Your contract — already signed by Bitshala — is in the Drive folder. Add your signature and upload the signed copy back to the same folder. Make sure the contract date matches the date in the contract document.

2. Submit Your W-8BEN Form
   We require a completed W-8BEN form for U.S. tax compliance on monthly payouts. Download the form from https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/fw8ben.pdf, fill it out (India-specific guidance below), and upload the completed form to the Drive folder.

3. Share Account Details
   Monthly payments are processed through Skydo. You'll receive a separate email from Skydo with a form for your account and contact info — please fill it in.

---

Reference: W-8BEN Form — India-Specific Guidance

Use this if you're filing from India. Skip if it doesn't apply.
Form: https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/fw8ben.pdf

Part I — Identification of Beneficial Owner
- 1: Your full name
- 2: Your country of citizenship
- 3: Full street address — city, state/province, postal code, country
- 4: Optional, only if mailing address differs from line 3
- 5: Leave blank (unless you have a U.S. tax ID)
- 6a: Your PAN card or relevant tax ID
- 6b: Leave blank
- 7: Date of birth (MM-DD-YYYY)

Part II — Claim of Tax Treaty Benefits
- 9a: India
- 10: Article 15 (Independent Personal Services) of the treaty on line 9 — claims a 0% withholding rate.
- Additional conditions: "Beneficial owner has a permanent establishment only in India and all work is done in India as per Article 5 (Permanent Establishment)."

Part III — Certification
- Sign, date, and complete the form.

